rComments: Does not answer questions by email, or takes weeks to answer. Quite disrespectful. He is hard to follow in class, goes on long examples that don't really lead anywhere and then moves on suddenly, leaving you wondering where you are in your notes. His final exam was long and tedious. Did not sympathize with students at all, especially during COVID.

Not the most engaging professor but the material he taught was interesting. The midterm is a take home with T/F questions and justifications with long answers and the final was supposed to be in person but because of COVID it was similar to the midterm but did not have the long answer portion.

Clearly a very intelligent professor. If you put in the time to come to class and follow along as he lectures, you will do well on the evaluations. His explanations are very clear and organized -- easily followed. Wish he taught more courses, would definitely take more.
I expected to get close to perfect on the first exam and ended up failing it... I dropped the course. I do not recommend him.
Very boring and repeats way too much. Goes on and on about the same stuff. Avoid if possible
